<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0597 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author rises the question how far the courts are responsible for theconcretisation of legal environmental terms and technological standards.Based on the Wyhl decision of the Federal Administrative Court and otherdecisions he comes to the conclusion that in this field the judicialcontrol concerning new technologies is reduced.</TEXT></DOC>